BigCommerce Catalog API

API and SDK Documentation

Version: 3.0.0b

A Swagger Document for the BigCommmerce API V3.

Catalog

catalogSummaryGet

Returns a lightweight inventory summary from the BigCommerce Catalog. 


/catalog/summary

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
curl -X get "https://api.bigcommerce.com/stores/{{store_id}}/v3/catalog/summary"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CatalogApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CatalogApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        try {
            CatalogSummaryResponse result = apiInstance.catalogSummaryGet();
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#catalogSummaryGet");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

createBrandImage

Creates an image on a `Brand`. Publicly accessible URLs and files (form post) are valid parameters. 


/catalog/brands/{brand_id}/image

Usage and SDK Samples

  • Curl
  • Java
  • Android
  • Obj-C
  • JavaScript
  • C#
  • PHP
curl -X post "https://api.bigcommerce.com/stores/{{store_id}}/v3/catalog/brands/{brand_id}/image"
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CatalogApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CatalogApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        Integer brandId = 56; // Integer | The ID of the `Brand` to which the image is being attached.

        File imageFile = /path/to/file.txt; // File | An image file. Supported MIME types include GIF, JPEG, and PNG.

        try {
            ImageResponse result = apiInstance.createBrandImage(brandId, imageFile);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#createBrandImage");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Path parameters
Name Description
brandId*
Form parameters
Name Description
imageFile*

Responses

Status: 200 - A ResourceImage and metadata.

  • Schema

Status: 404 - The resource was not found.

  • Schema

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CatalogApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CatalogApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        BigDecimal brandId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Brand` to which the resource belongs.

        Metafield metafield = ; // Metafield | A `Metafield` object.

        String key = key_example; // String | Filter based on a metafield's key.

        String namespace = namespace_example; // String | Filter based on a metafield's key.

        try {
            MetafieldResponse result = apiInstance.createBrandMetafield(brandId, metafield, key, namespace);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#createBrandMetafield");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

Name Description

Name Description

Query parameters
Name Description

namespace

Responses

Status: 200 - A `Metafield` object.

  • Schema

Status: 409 - The `Metafield` was in conflict with another `Metafield`. This can be the result of duplicate unique key combination of the app's client id, namespace, key, resource_type, and resource_id.

  • Schema

Status: 422 - The `Metafield` was not valid. This is the result of missing required fields, or of invalid data. See the response for more details.

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        BigDecimal productId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Product` to which the resource belongs.

        BigDecimal variantId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Variant` to which the resource belongs.

        Metafield metafield = ; // Metafield | A `Metafield` object.

        try {
            MetafieldResponse result = apiInstance.createVariantMetafield(productId, variantId, metafield);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#createVariantMetafield");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}
BigDecimal *productId = 3.4; // The ID of the `Product` to which the resource belongs.

BigDecimal *variantId = 3.4; // The ID of the `Variant` to which the resource belongs.

Metafield *metafield = ; // A `Metafield` object.


CatalogApi *apiInstance = [[CatalogApi alloc] init];

[apiInstance createVariantMetafieldWith:productId
    variantId:variantId
    metafield:metafield
              completionHandler: ^(MetafieldResponse output, NSError* error) {
                            if (output) {
                                NSLog(@"%@", output);
                            }
                            if (error) {
                                NSLog(@"Error: %@", error);
                            }
                        }];

Responses

Status: 200 - A `Metafield` object.

  • Schema

Status: 409 - The `Metafield` was in conflict with another `Metafield`. This can be the result of duplicate unique-key combinations of the app's client id, namespace, key, resource_type, and resource_id.

  • Schema

Status: 422 - The `Metafield` was not valid. This is the result of missing required fields, or of invalid data. See the response for more details.

deleteProducts

Deletes one or more `Product` objects from the BigCommerce Catalog 


/catalog/products

  • Android

curl -X delete "https://api.bigcommerce.com/stores/{{store_id}}/v3/catalog/products?name=&sku=&price=&weight=&condition=&brandId=&dateModified=&dateLastImported=&isVisible=&isFeatured=&inventoryLevel=&totalSold=&type=&categories=&keyword="
import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CatalogApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CatalogApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        String name = name_example; // String | Filter items by name.

        String sku = sku_example; // String | Filter items by sku.

        BigDecimal price = 3.4; // BigDecimal | Filter items by price.

        BigDecimal weight = 3.4; // BigDecimal | Filter items by weight.

        Integer condition = 56; // Integer | Filter items by condition.

        Integer brandId = 56; // Integer | Filter items by brand_id.

        String dateModified = dateModified_example; // String | Filter items by date_modified.

        String dateLastImported = dateLastImported_example; // String | Filter items by date_last_imported.

        Integer isVisible = 56; // Integer | Filter items by is_visible.

        Integer isFeatured = 56; // Integer | Filter items by is_featured.

        Integer inventoryLevel = 56; // Integer | Filter items by inventory_level.

        Integer totalSold = 56; // Integer | Filter items by total_sold.

        String type = type_example; // String | Filter items by type: `physical` or `digital`.

        Integer categories = 56; // Integer | Filter items by categories.

        String keyword = keyword_example; // String | Filter items by keywords found in the name, description, sku, keywords, or brand name.

        try {
            apiInstance.deleteProducts(name, sku, price, weight, condition, brandId, dateModified, dateLastImported, isVisible, isFeatured, inventoryLevel, totalSold, type, categories, keyword);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#deleteProducts");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        Integer id = 56; // Integer | Filter items by id.

        String name = name_example; // String | Filter items by name.

        String sku = sku_example; // String | Filter items by sku.

        String upc = upc_example; // String | Filter items by upc.

        BigDecimal price = 3.4; // BigDecimal | Filter items by price.

        BigDecimal weight = 3.4; // BigDecimal | Filter items by weight.

        Integer condition = 56; // Integer | Filter items by condition.

        Integer brandId = 56; // Integer | Filter items by brand_id.

        String dateModified = dateModified_example; // String | Filter items by date_modified.

        String dateLastImported = dateLastImported_example; // String | Filter items by date_last_imported.

        Integer isVisible = 56; // Integer | Filter items by is_visible.

        Integer isFeatured = 56; // Integer | Filter items by is_featured.

        Integer isFreeShipping = 56; // Integer | Filter items by is_free_shipping.

        Integer inventoryLevel = 56; // Integer | Filter items by inventory_level.

        Integer inventoryLow = 56; // Integer | Filter items by inventory_low; values: 1, 0.

        Integer outOfStock = 56; // Integer | Filter items by out_of_stock. To enable the filter, pass `out_of_stock`=`1`.

        Integer totalSold = 56; // Integer | Filter items by total_sold.

        String type = type_example; // String | Filter items by type: `physical` or `digital`.

        Integer categories = 56; // Integer | Filter items by categories.

        String keyword = keyword_example; // String | Filter items by keywords found in the name, description, sku, keywords, or brand name.

        String keywordContext = keywordContext_example; // String | Set context for a product search.

        String include = include_example; // String | Include sub-resources on a product, with a comma-separated list. Valid expansions currently include `variants`, `images`, `custom_fields`, and `bulk_pricing_rules`.

        String availability = availability_example; // String | Filter items by availability. Values are: available, disabled, preorder.

        Integer page = 56; // Integer | Control the page in a limited list of products.

        Integer limit = 56; // Integer | Control the items per page.

        String direction = direction_example; // String | Sort direction. Values are: asc, desc.

        String sort = sort_example; // String | Field name to sort by.
Values: id, name, sku, price, date_modified, date_last_imported, inventory_level, is_visible.

        try {
            ProductCollectionResponse result = apiInstance.getProducts(id, name, sku, upc, price, weight, condition, brandId, dateModified, dateLastImported, isVisible, isFeatured, isFreeShipping, inventoryLevel, inventoryLow, outOfStock, totalSold, type, categories, keyword, keywordContext, include, availability, page, limit, direction, sort);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#getProducts");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CatalogApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CatalogApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        BigDecimal productId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Product` to which the resource belongs.

        BigDecimal variantId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Variant` to which the resource belongs.

        try {
            VariantResponse result = apiInstance.getVariantById(productId, variantId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#getVariantById");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
}

getVariantMetafieldByProductIdAndVariantId

Gets a `Metafield`, by product_id and variant_id. 


/catalog/products/{product_id}/variants/{variant_id}/metafields/{metafield_id}

import io.swagger.client.*;
import io.swagger.client.auth.*;
import io.swagger.client.model.*;
import io.swagger.client.api.CatalogApi;

import java.io.File;
import java.util.*;

public class CatalogApiExample {

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        
        CatalogApi apiInstance = new CatalogApi();
        BigDecimal metafieldId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Metafield`.

        BigDecimal productId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Product` to which the resource belongs.

        BigDecimal variantId = 3.4; // BigDecimal | The ID of the `Variant` to which the resource belongs.

        try {
            Metafield result = apiInstance.getVariantMetafieldByProductIdAndVariantId(metafieldId, productId, variantId);
            System.out.println(result);
        } catch (ApiException e) {
            System.err.println("Exception when calling CatalogApi#getVariantMetafieldByProductIdAndVariantId");
            e.printStackTrace();
        }
    }
